<br>
***********<br>
Long Version<br>
***********<br>
<br>
Kargak Redblade is standing next to a Dwarf named Wenden in East Freeport. To get to them, head in the gate from North Ro and follow the left wall. They both start the quest. <br>
<br>
Hilt # 1 - Jeweled Dragon Head Hilt<br>
-Unjeweled dragon head hilt (spawning on the lake floor underneath the 3 aviak spawn tower)<br>
-Diamond (purchase from players)<br>
-Black Sapphire (purchase from players or vendors)<br>
-Jacinth (purchase from players or vendors)<br>
-Take the Unjeweled dragon head hilt Diamond, Jacinth, and black Saphire to the dwarf Wenden. Hand him all 4 items you will receive the Jeweled Dragon Head Hilt. <br>
<br>
Hilt #2 - Finely Crafted Dragon Head Hilt <br>
-At the base of the king piece, there is a small bag dropped on the ground - pick it up and you get the Damaged Dragon Head Hilt (at the Chess Board in the Timorous Deep)<br>
-Ball of Everliving Golem, which is dropped by Fright, Dread or Terror (on the Plane of Fear)<br>
-Kill the Mountin Giant Patriarch in the Dreadlands to receive the Giant Monocle. Give the Monocle to Mentrax Mountainbone (located by the mine entrance inside the Giant Fort in Frontier Mountains) to receive Rejesium Ore.<br>
-Hand the Rejesium Ore, Ball of Everliving Golem and Damaged Dragon Head Hilt to Wenden and he will give you the Finely Crafted Dragon Head Hilt<br>
<br>
Sword Blade # 1 - Ancient Sword Blade<br>
-Talk to Denken Strongpick, on aviak island in the Ocean of Tears. He'll tell you what he wants for this rusty old blade he found on the ocean floor: <br>
a) Purchase a keg of vox tail ale (can be found in Freeport Port Authority)<br>
b) Block of Permafrost (dropped by Ice Giants in Permafrost)<br>
NOTE: Kill Goblins wizards here for the frozen goblin heart which you will need later<br>
c) 2 Rebreathers (tinkered by gnomes, which you will have to purchase)<br>
-Turn the 2 Rebreathers, the keg of vox tail ale, and the Block of Permafrost in to the dwarf and you will get the 1st blade. <br>
<br>
Sword Blade # 2 - Ancient Blade<br>
-This item is rarely dropped by the Queen of Chardok<br>
<br>
The Red Scabbard<br>
-Talk to Kargak Redblade in East Freeport - next to Wenden and say [I will do you a favor]. You get a letter (a wax sealed note). Take this letter to an Ogre in Ferrott named Oknoggin. He hangs out between the Stone Bridge and the Fallen Totem. Hand him the letter and he gives you a Tiny Lute.<br>
-Run back to East Freeport and give the Tiny Lute to Kargek Redblade. In turn, he gives you a book. Now take the book over to his brother Tenal Redblade in East Karana, who is at the very end of the canyon next to the ramp to Highpass. Hand Tenal Redblade the book, and he gives you a Frozen War Totem. <br>
-Hand him back the Totem and the Frozen Goblin Heart from Permafrost and he gives you back the Totem of Fiery War. <br>
-Kill a Green Dragon for a Green Dragon Scale (i.e., Severlious in the Emerald Jungle)<br>
-Kill a Red Dragon for a Red Dragon Scale (e.g., Lord Nagafen in Sol B or Talendor in Skyfire)<br>
-Give Tenal Redblade the Totem of Fiery War, Green Dragon Scale, and Red Dragon Scale to receive the The Mark of the Sword.<br>
-Get the Hand of the Maestro from the Maestro of Rancor on the Plane of Hate.<br>
-Hand Tenal Redblade the Mark of the Sword and the Hand of the Maestro and he gives you a note to Kargek.<br>
-Head to the Plane of Air and kill the Spiroc Lord to receive the Spiroc Wingblade<br>
-Give Kargek the note to Kargek and the Wingblade to receive the Red Scabbard and the Instructions to assemble the final sword<br>
<br>
Assemble the Jagged Blade of War as instructed<br>
